    <title>Combined summary - Making (some) channel limits dynamic</title>
    <updated>2023-06-03T02:17:47.998032+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/lightning-dev/2020-October/002814.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>The proposal is suggesting the addition of tlv records in `commitment_signed` which would inform the channel peer that certain fields' values are changing. This idea fits well with the "parameter re-negotiation" portion of the loose Dynamic commitments proposal. Both parties would be able to propose, accept or deny updates to flow control parameters leading to increased security of a channel. The dynamic HTLC bandwidth allocation mechanism would mitigate various classes of attacks and provide forwarding nodes more control over their allocated bandwidth. Additionally, it could implement a form of "slow start" protocol for new peers.Another key value that should be dynamic to protect against future unexpected events is the dust limit.</summary>
